-# Submission Alignment Guide
-
-This guide turns the current codebase into a clean marking story for the viva/demo.
-
-## What To Show First
-
-1. Login using one of the seeded users from `DataInitializer`.
-2. Open the dashboard and point out the role-aware navigation.
-3. Demo resource CRUD, smart search, and CSV import.
-4. Demo booking creation, conflict handling, and approval/rejection.
-5. Demo maintenance ticket creation, assignment, comments, and SLA details.
-6. Open notifications and preferences.
-7. Show the CI workflow and explain backend/frontend verification.
-
-## Requirement Coverage
-
-| Area | Evidence in the repo | What to say in the presentation |
-| --- | --- | --- |
-| Authentication and role control | `src/main/java/com/campus/smart_campus/controller/AuthController.java`, `src/main/java/com/campus/smart_campus/service/AuthService.java`, `src/main/java/com/campus/smart_campus/config/AuthInterceptor.java` | The app uses session-based login, protected endpoints, and role-aware UI access. |
-| Resource management | `src/main/java/com/campus/smart_campus/controller/ResourceController.java`, `src/main/java/com/campus/smart_campus/service/ResourceService.java` | Resources can be created, updated, deleted, searched, and filtered. |
-| Booking workflow | `src/main/java/com/campus/smart_campus/controller/BookingController.java`, `src/main/java/com/campus/smart_campus/service/BookingService.java` | The booking flow supports pending, approve, reject, cancel, and conflict checks. |
-| Maintenance workflow | `src/main/java/com/campus/smart_campus/controller/MaintenanceController.java`, `src/main/java/com/campus/smart_campus/service/MaintenanceService.java` | Tickets support status updates, technician assignment, comments, attachments, and SLA tracking. |
-| Notifications | `src/main/java/com/campus/smart_campus/controller/NotificationController.java`, `src/main/java/com/campus/smart_campus/service/NotificationService.java` | Notifications and preferences are managed in-app and mirrored in the header badge. |
-| Dashboard and analytics | `src/main/java/com/campus/smart_campus/controller/DashboardController.java`, `src/main/java/com/campus/smart_campus/service/DashboardService.java`, `src/main/java/com/campus/smart_campus/dto/DashboardSummary.java` | The dashboard gives a quick operational overview with counts and status summaries. |
-| Frontend experience | `frontend/src/PortalApp.tsx`, `frontend/src/components/Header.tsx`, `frontend/src/portal.css` | The UI is responsive, role-aware, and organized around panels and workflow cards. |
-| CI and build verification | `.github/workflows/ci.yml` | The repository includes a GitHub Actions pipeline for backend tests and frontend builds. |
-
-## Strong Demo Talking Points
-
-- The backend follows a layered structure: controller, service, repository, DTO, and model.
-- The app uses seeded demo data so the markers can see the workflows immediately.
-- The system is modular enough to map cleanly to a 4-member project division.
-- The frontend is purpose-built for operations work, with forms, queues, badges, and dashboards rather than a generic CRUD shell.
-
-## Honest Notes
-
-- The current implementation is session-based authentication with an OAuth-compatible route name for documentation and demo purposes.
-- If your rubric expects a live third-party OAuth provider, that would be a separate integration step.
-- If you need to present only implemented features, keep the demo focused on the flows listed above.
-
